A short strafe map (~30sec)

- have fun -

Gameplay:  bhop_warmzsteon is a large map with 8 separate levels. The teleports to the levels allow you to keep your speed expect for 1 because it would open up a skip to a whole section. It is made to be played on autohop settings. 

Materials:  All of the textures are default. Pcpie's booster prefab was used for boosters. https://gamebanana.com/prefabs/7118

info/problems:  I made this map back in 2015-2016 but never released it. I didn't really understand how to do lighting then so some levels have light entities spammed everywhere.  I'm releasing it now because I think some people will have fun with it.

_sText:
Hello!

This is my second map! (Let's say first since the first one was me fooling around with brushes and entities). I did my best to try and make a decent bhop map which I think I partially succeeded at but there's still lots of improvements to be done and I'd like your feedback to get there!

The map consists of 3 stages where 2 are really short and the third is just above the short timespand in which I did the map in about a minute and thirty seconds, give it a try and let me know what I can improve on :')

Hello!

On this map are all the complexities of the complex, from the simplest to the most complex.

The map has more than 20 new levels.

At the beginning of the map there is a musical accompaniment with the name of the song in the center of the screen.

At the end of the card there is music, it will not interrupt or mix the music that is in the beginning.

Design and textures on the map look good and will not be nervous.

The whole map has good lighting, there are no mistakes with textures.

I really hope that you will enjoy playing on my map!

Have a good game!

**Short and quite simple bhop map with some kz mixed in.**

Original map was created by Yeckoh for our Zombie Master 1 bunnyhop server back in 2012. The intention was to create a really simple map that even new bhoppers could beat. We then decided to port it to CSS (along with some others maybe :>). We improved on it a little and then forgot about it for a while... Here it is!

I am releasing it on behalf of Yeckoh.
